<h3>Question 10</h3>
<div><p><p>Based on your experience as an IT professional, write instructions for new aspirants, explaining how to begin a career in this field.</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p>For the last five years, l have been developing my skills and abilities as a professional within top companies in Nepal. I graduated from ABC College of IT, Kathmandu. So, I would like to transfer my skills and experiences to new aspirants by sharing my knowledge and suggestions to begin a career in this field.</p>
<p>In IT, you need a long-term vision or goal and you should be always learning information technology as it is a growing and rapidly changing field of study as compared to other fields of study. Both dedication and discipline are the first skills to become an IT professional. If you have such skills, you are able to learn other technical skills such as programming through as recent information is available along with other technical knowledge.</p>
<p>After the development of technical skills, you need to learn social skills such as communication, cooperation, participation, and many other skills. With these skills, you can take help from others and help yourself to others along with developing networking skills that can make your life easier to grow.</p>
<p>The other skill you need to become a successful professional is business communication and technical writing. With these skills, you can promote and share your knowledge among people all around the world while sitting in the remote corner of your house or accommodation. In conclusion, the IT field is all about problem-solving skills and you can utilize it to facilitate the lifestyle of the people in your community.</p>
</div>
